[[File:ChristianityBranches-2.svg|thumb]]
{{NOT|希臘教會}}

'''希臘正教會'''（{{lang-el|Ελληνορθόδοξη Εκκλησία}}，{{lang-en|Greek Orthodox Church}}）是[[羅馬帝國|羅馬帝國]]國家教會分裂後，[[正教會|羅馬正教會]]的幾個教會統稱<ref>Demetrios J. Constantelos, Understanding the Greek Orthodox Church, Holy Cross Orthodox Press 3rd edition (March 28, 2005)</ref><ref>L. Rushton, Doves and magpies: village women in the Greek Orthodox Church Women's religious experience, Croom Helm, 1983</ref><ref>Paul Yuzyk, The [[Ukrainian_Orthodox_Church_of_Canada|Ukrainian Orthodox Church of Canada]], 1918–1951, University of Ottawa Press, 1981</ref>，其神學根植於早期[[教父_(基督教歷史)|教父]]以及[[拜占庭|拜占庭]]文化，[[基督教禮拜儀式|禮拜儀式]]使用[[通用希臘語|通用希臘語]]<ref>Demetrios J. Constantelos, The Greek Orthodox Church: faith, history, and practice, Seabury Press, 1967</ref><ref>Daniel B. Wallace: {{cite book |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=XlqoTVsk2wcC&printsec=frontcover&lr=#PPA12,M1 |title = Greek Grammar Beyond the Basics: An Exegetical Syntax of the New Testament, page 12, |access-date = 2015-10-30 |archive-date = 2020-10-10 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201010134041/https://books.google.com/books?id=XlqoTVsk2wcC&printsec=frontcover&lr=#PPA12,M1 |dead-url = no }} Zondervan, 1997.</ref><ref>Robert H. Stein: {{cite book |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=mRDCqEHDqDEC&pg=PA4#v=onepage&q&f=false |title = The method and message of Jesus' teachings, page 4, |access-date = 2015-10-30 |archive-date = 2020-10-10 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201010134046/https://books.google.com/books?id=mRDCqEHDqDEC&pg=PA4#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url = no }} Westminster John Knox Press, 1994.</ref>。與[[普世牧首|普世牧首]][[共融|共融]]。其起源於近東的[[早期基督教|早期基督教]]以及[[拜占庭帝國|拜占庭帝國]]，当代東正教[[修道_(基督教)|修道活动]]最重要的中心為在[[埃及|埃及]][[西奈半島|西奈半島]]的[[聖凱瑟琳修道院|聖凱瑟琳修道院]]和以及[[馬其頓共和國|馬其頓]]的[[阿索斯山|阿索斯山]]。

[[東西教會大分裂|東西教會大分裂]]時與[[天主教會|羅馬天主教會]]各分東西，並與[[斯拉夫人|斯拉夫]]等正教會共融成為[[東正教會|東正教會]]。

== 沿革 ==
希臘正教的起源可以追溯到公元一世紀的[[巴尔干半岛|巴爾幹]]和[[中东|中東地區]]教會<ref name="ChafetzEbaugh2000">{{cite book|author1=Janet Saltzman Chafetz|author2=Helen Rose Ebaugh|title=Religion and the New Immigrants: Continuities and Adaptations in Immigrant Congregations|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AT57AAAAQBAJ&pg=PA155|accessdate=2 September 2013|date=18 October 2000|publisher=AltaMira Press|isbn=978-0-7591-1712-9|page=155|quote=The distinctive characteristics of the Greek Orthodox Church are its sense of continuity with the ancient Church of Christ and the Apostles and its changelessness. The Orthodox church traces its existence, through the ordinatinon of Bishops. directly back to the Apostles and through them to Jesus.|archive-date=2020-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201010134051/https://books.google.com/books?id=AT57AAAAQBAJ&pg=PA155|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="BruyneelPadgett2003">{{cite book|author1=Sally Bruyneel|author2=Alan G. Padgett|title=Introducing Christianity|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HhratxerbcwC&pg=PA7|accessdate=2 September 2013|year=2003|publisher=Orbis Books|isbn=978-1-60833-134-5|page=7|quote=The Eastern Orthodox and thye Roman Catholic Churches are the oldest with roots going back to the earliest Christian groups.|archive-date=2020-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201010142853/https://books.google.com/books?id=HhratxerbcwC&pg=PA7|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="HubbardHatfield2007">{{cite book|author1=Benjamin Jerome Hubbard|author2=John T. Hatfield|author3=James A. Santucci|title=An Educator's Classroom Guide to America's Religious Beliefs and Practices|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UWBIuX7TPk8C&pg=PA63|accessdate=2 September 2013|year=2007|publisher=Libraries Unlimited|isbn=978-1-59158-409-4|page=63|quote=The Orthodox Church traces its origins to the churches founded by the apostles in the Middle East and the Balkans in the first century.|archive-date=2020-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201010134100/https://books.google.com/books?id=UWBIuX7TPk8C&pg=PA63|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Plummer2012">{{cite book|author=Robert L. Plummer|title=Journeys of Faith: Evangelicalism, Eastern Orthodoxy, Catholicism and Anglicanism|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IMhir6agIEcC&pg=PT128|accessdate=2 September 2013|date=6 March 2012|publisher=Zondervan|isbn=978-0-310-41671-5|page=128|quote=Catholicism holds that if a Church claims to be Christian, then it must be able to show that its leaders-its bishops and its presbyters (or priests)- are successors of the apostles. That is why the Catholic Church accepts Eastern Orthodox ordinations and sacraments as valid, even though Eastern Orthodoxy is not in full communion with Rome.|archive-date=2020-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201010134104/https://books.google.com/books?id=IMhir6agIEcC&pg=PT128|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="DyrnessKärkkäinen2009">{{cite book|author1=William A. Dyrness|author2=Veli-Matti Kärkkäinen|title=Global Dictionary of Theology: A Resource for the Worldwide Church|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ncqkZnDSeo4C&pg=PA244|accessdate=2 September 2013|date=25 September 2009|publisher=InterVarsity Press|isbn=978-0-8308-7811-6|page=244|quote=This connection is apparent through the historical succession of bishops of churches in a particular geographic locale and by fidelity to the teachings of the apostles (cf. Acts 2:42) and life as it developed in the patristic tradition and was articulated by the seven ecumenical councils.|archive-date=2020-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201120044552/https://books.google.com/books?id=ncqkZnDSeo4C&pg=PA244|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Campbell2010">{{cite book|author=Heidi A Campbell|title=When Religion Meets New Media|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UqOKUVsazmkC&pg=PA13|accessdate=2 September 2013|date=22 March 2010|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0-203-69537-1|page=13|quote=There are three branches within Christianity: Catholic, Eastern Orthodox, and Protestant. ... The Christian church draws its lineage and roots from the time of Jesus Christ and the apostles in CE 25–30 and the birth of the Church at Pentecost in ...|archive-date=2020-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201010134113/https://books.google.com/books?id=UqOKUVsazmkC&pg=PA13|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Doniger1999">{{cite book|author=Wendy Doniger|title=Merriam-Webster's Encyclopedia of World Religions|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZP_f9icf2roC&pg=PA309|accessdate=2 September 2013|date=January 1999|publisher=Merriam-Webster|isbn=978-0-87779-044-0|page=309|quote=EASTERN ORTHODOXY, one of the major branches of CHRISTIANITY, characterized by its continuity with the apostolic church, its liturgy, and its territorial churches.|archive-date=2020-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201010134121/https://books.google.com/books?id=ZP_f9icf2roC&pg=PA309|dead-url=no}}</ref>，它保留了許多古代教會的傳統。<ref name="Doniger1999"/>希臘正教以及普世正教會不像[[天主教|天主教]]一樣以單一主教管轄，如[[教宗|教宗]]，而是由多個自主教會組成一個群集。並由君士坦丁堡普世牧首為平等的精神領袖。

希臘正教重視與其他[[正教會|東正教]]教會（如俄羅斯東正教）的團結與交流。東正教有著共同的[[宗教教義|教義]]和崇拜[[仪式|儀式]]，他們認為自己不是一個個獨立的教會，而是作為同一個教會的一小部份。希臘正教最著名的是其保有豐富意象的傳統（參見：[[拜占庭式建筑|拜占庭藝術]]）、對[[上帝|上帝]]和[[聖母|聖母]]的崇拜、以及使用可以追溯到公元四世紀，由[[約翰一世_(君士坦丁堡牧首)|聖約翰]]創立的富有東正教特色的[[事奉聖禮|事奉聖禮]]。

現今有部分希臘東正教徒，其祖先歷史可以追溯到拜占庭和[[奧斯曼王朝|奧斯曼]]時期，他們的祖先使用[[阿拉伯语|阿拉伯語]]或[[希腊语|希臘語]]，生活在[[土耳其|土耳其]]南部、[[以色列|以色列]]、[[巴勒斯坦国|巴勒斯坦]]、[[伊拉克|伊拉克]]、[[叙利亚|敘利亞]]、[[黎巴嫩|黎巴嫩]]、[[约旦|約旦]]和[[埃及|埃及]]。他們使用阿拉伯語且保持了拜占庭的希臘文化傳統。<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=JBqWbDmFsfEC&pg=PA159&dq=Yunastan&lr= ''Byzantium'' in ''Encyclopedia of historians and historical writing'' Vol. 1, Kelly Boyd (ed.), Fitzroy Dearborn publishers, 1999] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JBqWbDmFsfEC&pg=PA159&dq=Yunastan&lr= |date=20190610062333 }} ISBN 978-1-884964-33-6</ref><ref>Edwin Pears, The destruction of the Greek Empire and the story of the capture of Constantinople by the Turks, Haskell House, 1968</ref><ref name="Millar 2006 279 pages">{{cite book
  | last =Millar
  | first =Fergus
  | title =A Greek Roman Empire : power and belief under Theodosius II (408–450)
  | url =https://archive.org/details/greekromanempire00ferg
  | publisher =University of California Press
  | year =2006
  | isbn = 0-520-24703-5
  | page= [https://archive.org/details/greekromanempire00ferg/page/279 279] pages }}</ref>君士坦丁堡在基督教創立以來的前八個世紀，其在[[羅馬帝國|羅馬帝國]]的影響範圍內是基督教最重要的智慧，文化和社會發展與傳承中心<ref name="Millar 2006 279 pages"/><ref>Tanner, Norman P. The Councils of the Church, ISBN 978-0-8245-1904-9</ref><ref>The Byzantine legacy in the Orthodox Church by John Meyendorff – 1982</ref><ref>Hugh Wybrew, The Orthodox liturgy: the development of the eucharistic liturgy in the Byzantine rite – 1990</ref>，而今日希臘正教的大多數儀式、傳統和做法至今仍然在[[君士坦丁堡|君士坦丁堡]]教會運作。於公元10世紀，希臘正教使得[[斯拉夫人|斯拉夫民族]]開始發展文明以及與其他歐洲國家接觸，並發展出了斯拉夫正教會禮儀。<ref>The Christian Churches of the East, Vol. II: Churches Not in Communion with Rome by Donald Attwater – 1962</ref><ref>J Meyendorff, Byzantine Theology: Historical Trends and Doctrinal Themes (1987)</ref> <ref name="ReferenceA">Joan M. Hussey, The Orthodox Church in the Byzantine Empire, 1990</ref><ref name="ReferenceA"/><ref name="ReferenceB">A. P. Vlasto, Entry of Slavs Christendom – 1970</ref><ref name="ReferenceB"/><ref>Andreĭ Lazarov Pantev, Bŭlgarska istorii︠a︡ v evropeĭski kontekst – 2000</ref>

